The paper deals with the optimization of beamforming in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and network optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with network optimization and control, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves system-level design and control, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves spatial multiplexing and diversity, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimization algorithms and techniques, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
